b'Job Details
Description
The MedInsight engineering team develops an industry-leading software as a service data warehouse platform, analytical tools, and custom applications for healthcare providers, payers, community coalitions, and all payer claims database customers. We are looking for interns that are creative, passionate, enthusiastic and most importantly eager to learn. This internship is catered towards individuals that really want to know how it is to work in a growing software company. Interns will be will be assigned a senior engineer as their mentor and will be a full member of the engineering team.

Undergraduates only please.

What We Are Looking For

Above all else, we are interested in people that are excited about developing new solutions, working in a fast paced environment, and collaborating with individuals outside of the engineering team to solve problems. Most members of the engineering team wear numerous hats, so the ideal candidate is an innovative self-starter with a solid software development foundation, who is interested in working with our team of experienced developers to make a measurable impact. The healthcare technology space is constantly evolving, so it is essential for success that candidates be able to learn new processes/technologies and to adapt quickly. The Milliman MedInsight group is rapidly growing, so successful candidates will have opportunities to grow within their positions and within the larger team.

Skills and Experience

We prefer students entering their junior or senior year and are majoring in the following areas:

Computer Science
Engineering
Physical Sciences

Students that do not meet this criteria but think they are up for a challenge please feel free to apply. Below is a list of the skills and background that align with the projects that the team is currently working on or plans to work on in the near future.

An understanding of general Business Intelligence best practices, data warehousing, or relational database development;
Experience building solutions leveraging the cloud (Azure, AWS, etc.);
Experience working with large data sets;
Understanding of OLAP technologies (Analysis Services);
Experience with massively parallel processing (MPP) databases;
Healthcare concepts and data experience;
Healthcare informatics, analytics, and reporting knowledge;
SharePoint development or administration experience;
C# or similar object oriented programming language experience;
Functional programming experience;
Understanding of design patterns and when to use them;
General web development skills/experience (CSS, HTML, JavaScript);
PowerShell or other scripting skills or experience; and
Windows server/network administration skills.

About Milliman & MedInsight

Milliman is one of the world\xe2\x80\x99s largest independent professional services firms. Founded in 1947, the firm provides consulting services to clients in four practice areas: healthcare, life insurance and financial services, employee benefits and pensions, and property and casualty insurance. Today, Milliman has more than 3,500 employees, $1 billion in annual revenue, and more than 60 offices worldwide.

Milliman MedInsight is one of the healthcare industry\xe2\x80\x99s most highly regarded platforms for data warehousing and healthcare analytics, with a purpose of empowering easy, data-driven decision-making on important healthcare questions.
MedInsight solutions have been adopted by over 300 health plans, employers, at-risk providers and ACOs, state governments, community health coalitions, and third-party administrators. MedInsight also offers standalone products that provide preconfigured or custom reporting and data configurations that can address specific business needs.

We are currently working mostly remote due to COVID restrictions, but the MedInsight home office is based in Seattle, WA.
